feed2.name: Jennifer Lawrence
feed2.comment: You can't just ask customers what they want and then try to give that to them. By the time you get it built, they'll want something new.

feed3.name: Steve Jobs
feed3.comment: It's really hard to design products by focus groups. A lot of times, people don't know what they want until you show it to them.

feed4.name: Stephenie Meyer
feed4.comment: When you give everyone a voice and give people power, the system usually ends up in a really good place. So, what we view our role as, is giving people that power.
